<font face="verdana"> 
<div> 
<img src="http://www.nyc.gov/html/sbs/images/misc/agency_branding_02.gif"> 
<b><h2> Individual Training Grants Available for the Following Positions:</h2></b> 
<br><b> Unarmed Security Guards</b> 
<ul> 
<b>Minimum Requirements:</b> 
<ul> 
<li> High School Diploma or GED</li> 
<li> 6 Months of work experience in a customer service setting or related field, and must pass a background check</li> 
<li> </li>
</ul> 
<b>Who is eligible to apply for an Individual Training Grant?</b> 
<ul> 
<li>Must be actively looking for employment or currently employed and earning less than $62,894 a year </li> 
<li>Must be ready to work immediately after training</li>
<li>Must meet or exceed minimum requirements</li> 
<li>Must be at least 18 years old</li> 
<li> &gt;
</ul> 
<b>How can I apply for an Individual Training Grant?</b> 
<ul> 
<li>The application process is highly selective. At each step you will receive approval to move forward or referral to other services. Completing an application does not guarantee receipt of an ITG.</li> 
</ul> 
<p><b>In order to apply and be considered for the training grant, interested candidates must attend an Orientation conducted by the Bronx Workforce1 Career Center and bring the following documents: High School Diploma or GED, Resume, Photo Id. </b><br>
</br><b>Date:</b>Monday thru Thursday, March , 2017<br>
<b>Check in:</b> 8:30 AM to 8:50 AM (No admittance after 8:50 AM) <br><br>
<b>Location:</b> 400 E FordhamRoad , Bronx NY 10458 8th floor<br><br>
<b>Directions:</b> By subway take the 4 or D train to Fordham Road Station or  by bus take the Bx17, Bx15 or Bx41 to Fordham Road&gt;Workforce1 is a service that attracts, prepares, and connects qualified candidates to job opportunities in New York City. We use a combination of recruitment expertise, industry knowledge, and services that strengthen candidates' employment prospects to make strong matches for job candidates and businesses alike.
<br><br>To learn more, visit <a href="http://www.nyc.gov/wf1recruitment" rel="nofollow">nyc.gov/wf1recruitment</a>. Don't forget to <a href="http://www.facebook.com/nycworkforce1" rel="nofollow">like us on Facebook</a>, follow <a href="http://twitter.com/nycworkforce1" rel="nofollow">@NYCWorkforce1</a>, and visit our <a href="http://nycworkforce1.org" rel="nofollow">Career Blog</a>.
<br><br> Equal opportunity employer/program. Auxiliary aids and services are available upon request to individuals with disabilities.
</p></div>
</font>
</li></ul>    </section>

